{
  "stem": "11179.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The harbor of Shanghai was controlled by the Japanese who had in '37 taken over the whole Northern China practically in the war with China.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Southern China, they never got.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But Northern China, they did.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Shanghai, they-- they-- they took part of  an international settlement, mainly where a lot of Japanese lived, civilians from before I believe, and annexed that to their area.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And on the other side of the river still was international settlement and the French concession.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The French concession was like a French colony.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The international settlement was run by a municipal government of nine people which were, they have to be, by their constitution or what, five British, two Americans, and two Japanese.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And we lived in the part we called [INAUDIBLE], which was taken over when the Japanese was bombed.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they wanted the Japanese to stop us to get through.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because there was about a 30 [INAUDIBLE], about a 30 mile river travel from-- from the-- from the sea through the Yangtze mouth to Shanghai to the [INAUDIBLE] river.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And on the way there, the Japanese custom [INAUDIBLE] came aboard.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they could have stopped us, but did not.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they wanted them to stop it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the Japanese took their good time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They didn't really want to do it at that time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they consulted a couple of very influential Jews-- and it is in the book there-- if it was all right.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they figured it was quite all right.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that happened in May 1939, before we-- before we-- we got on the ship.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We did not know this that they were [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the Japanese dragged it out, I think, till October, till they finally did close-- close it without money.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
